[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has 13 points and good 3-card support for NORTH's 1\H opening bid. 
But he should not bid 2NT since that bid promises 4+ cards in support. South must still insure 
they reach game, so he bids a forcing 2\C.

When NORTH next says 2NT SOUTH can jump to 4\H.

NOTE: if you used Jacoby 2NT and reached the 4\H game, give yourself credit anyway.}

